      "num": 1,
      "text": "Which professional is primarily responsible for investigating, documenting, and proving fraud for purposes of legal or disciplinary actions?",
      "tag": "Role of CFE",
      "options": [
        "A. Fraud examiner (CFE)",
        "B. Independent external auditor",
        "C. Financial controller",
        "D. Compliance analyst"
      ],
      "correct": 0,
      "justification_correct": "The fraud examiner is specifically defined by their focus on proving fraud, collecting evidence, interviewing suspects, and preparing cases for prosecution or disciplinary action. (ACFE Code of Professional Standards)",
      "justification_wrong": "External auditors verify financial statements; controllers manage financial records; compliance analysts monitor regulatory compliance — the CFE is the specialized fraud investigator.",
      "difficulty": "EASY",
      "legacy": true,
      "legacy_source": "financial_transactions/quiz_006_en.json"
    },
    {
      "num": 2,
      "text": "Which professional characteristic is most determinative in sustaining the credibility of a fraud examiner?",
      "tag": "Credibility",
      "options": [
        "A. Assertive posture and aggressive investigative approach",
        "B. Speed in completing engagements",
        "C. Impartiality in conclusions and process",
        "D. Hierarchical authority within the organization"
      ],
      "correct": 2,
      "justification_correct": "Impartiality ensures that conclusions are technically defensible and perceived as trustworthy by all involved parties. (ACFE Code of Professional Standards)",
      "justification_wrong": "Aggressiveness, speed, and hierarchical authority are not attributes that sustain the fraud examiner's professional credibility.",
      "difficulty": "STANDARD",
      "legacy": true,
      "legacy_source": "fraud_investigation/quiz_003_en.json"
    },
    {
      "num": 3,
      "text": "Which regulation governs the professional conduct standards of Certified Fraud Examiners?",
      "tag": "Professional Standards",
      "options": [
        "A. Generally Accepted Accounting Principles (GAAP)",
        "B. Generally Accepted Auditing Standards (GAAS)",
        "C. ACFE Code of Professional Ethics",
        "D. IRS Circular 230"
      ],
      "correct": 2,
      "justification_correct": "The ACFE Code of Professional Ethics establishes the standards of conduct, integrity, and objectivity governing CFE practice. (ACFE Code of Professional Standards)",
      "justification_wrong": "GAAP, GAAS, and tax regulations govern accounting and auditing practices, not the specific ethical standards of CFE certification.",
      "difficulty": "EASY",
      "legacy": true,
      "legacy_source": "fraud_investigation/quiz_003_en.json"
    },
    {
      "num": 4,
      "text": "Which concrete action demonstrates the application of the principle of due professional care?",
      "tag": "Due Professional Care",
      "options": [
        "A. Expedite conclusions to meet organizational deadlines",
        "B. Disregard inconsistencies of low apparent value",
        "C. Conduct a thorough and comprehensive evaluation of evidence",
        "D. Delegate investigative tasks entirely to the team"
      ],
      "correct": 2,
      "justification_correct": "Due professional care requires careful, complete, and competent evaluation of all relevant evidence, without shortcuts or oversimplifications. (ACFE Code of Professional Standards)",
      "justification_wrong": "Haste, disregarding inconsistencies, and full delegation are practices inconsistent with due professional care.",
      "difficulty": "STANDARD",
      "legacy": true,
      "legacy_source": "fraud_investigation/quiz_003_en.json"
    },
    {
      "num": 5,
      "text": "Which professional principle ensures the consistent and impartial application of investigative standards?",
      "tag": "Principles",
      "options": [
        "A. Institutional loyalty",
        "B. Confidentiality",
        "C. Professional judgment",
        "D. Objectivity"
      ],
      "correct": 3,
      "justification_correct": "Objectivity ensures that standards are applied fairly, impartially, and consistently, regardless of the parties involved. (ACFE Code of Professional Standards)",
