    },
    {
      "num": 6,
      "text": "A CFE discovers evidence of significant fraud by management but is instructed by the client to stop the investigation and report that no issues were found. What does the ACFE Code of Ethics require?",
      "tag": "Professional Ethics",
      "options": [
        "A. Terminate the investigation as instructed by the paying client",
        "B. Report the case to criminal authorities immediately",
        "C. Report findings truthfully and refuse to issue a misleading report",
        "D. Seek guidance from legal counsel before deciding"
      ],
      "correct": 2,
      "justification_correct": "The ACFE Code of Ethics requires CFEs to report findings truthfully and not participate in any illegal or improper activity—regardless of client instructions. (ACFE Code of Professional Ethics)",
